</p><p class="- topic/p ">This error is reported when the roll can not be initialized. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This is checked after a media roll is loaded, the media drawer is closed and only on the first use of the media from that roll. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> On a start print or feed of the media, the media is moved forward and backward for 2 times to determine feed forward parameters and the 1<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">st</sup> time to determine the radius. It should return with the leading edge positioned between MLO pinch and SE2. 
